snippet.textDisplay:
man, I was really looking forward to getting some unique effects for the G-max moves on the starters, maybe they'd have something awesome like the Origin Forme weather, and Rillaboom could have a new version of it that made grass types good for once by blocking their five weaknesses...
...instead we got "ignores abilities"...
Rillaboom gets strictly worse, since it lost the ability to set Grassy Terrain with STAB just to hit Shedinja. Cinderace and Inteleon also lose their ability to set weather and make their STAB stronger, but both of them have impressive movepools(which include coveted Flying attacks for speed boosts) so they dont change much.
guess we'll have to wait until their HAs drop for anything useful to get added to them...
snippet.textOriginal:
man, I was really looking forward to getting some unique effects for the G-max moves on the starters, maybe they'd have something awesome like the Origin Forme weather, and Rillaboom could have a new version of it that made grass types  good for once by blocking their *five* weaknesses...
...instead we got "ignores abilities"... 
Rillaboom gets strictly worse, since it lost the ability to set Grassy Terrain with STAB just to hit Shedinja. Cinderace and Inteleon also lose their ability to set weather and make their STAB stronger, but both of them have impressive movepools(which include coveted Flying attacks for speed boosts) so they dont change much.
guess we'll have to wait until their HAs drop for anything useful to get added to them...
